Service Resources Corp said its Chas.P. Young Co subsidiary, which has offered to acquire Sorg Incin a friendly merger at 22 dlrs per share, is willing toexplore the possibility that members of the Sorg family andother Sorg shareholders could continue to hold an equityposition in the combined company.    The company also said it has received a commitment for upto 66 mln dlrs in financing from Security Pacific Corp &lt;SPC>for the merger, the repayment of Sorg's bank debt and workingcapital of the combined company. Reuter&#3;